Package: miditoolsR
Type: Package
Title: Tools to create and play MIDI files
Version: 0.1.0.0001
Authors@R: person("Erich", "Neuwirth", , "erich.neuwirth@univie.ac.at", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: Midi files (a standard way to represent music as file) 
    are binary files and cannot be handled easily in R. 
    This toolkit allows to create midi files from dataframes
    by mapping variables to pitches, durations, volume,
    ans instruments.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1),
    dplyr
Imports:
    midicsvR,
    midiplayR,
    purrr,
    readr,
    stringr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
URL: https://github.com/neuwirthe/miditoolsR
BugReports: https://github.com/neuwirthe/miditoolsR/issues
